'''Bing Dwen Dwen''' ({{zh|c=冰墩墩|p=Bīng Dūn Dūn}}) is the [[List of Olympic mascots|official mascot]] of the [[2022 Winter Olympics]], and '''Shuey Rhon Rhon''' ({{zh|c=雪容融|p=Xuě Róng Róng}}) is the [[List of Paralympic mascots|official mascot]] of the [[2022 Winter Paralympics]]. The name of Bing Dwen Dwen possibly means ice ''hulu'', as 墩 (Dūn) in its name is a homophone of 礅 (Dūn) in the word 糖礅 in Tianjin dialect, meaning [[tanghulu]], the prototype of the mascot. Both events were held in [[Beijing]], the capital of [[China]].<ref name=bdd />

