The '''Olympic Green''' ({{zh|s=奥林匹克森林公园|l=Olympic Forest Park}}) is an [[Olympic Park]] in [[Chaoyang, Beijing|Chaoyang]], [[Beijing]], [[China]]. The three main facilities there include the [[National Stadium (China)|National Stadium (Bird's Nest)]], [[Water Cube]], and [[National Indoor Stadium]].

Olympic Green was originally constructed for the [[2008 Summer Olympics]] and the [[2008 Summer Paralympics]]. Since then, the streets around the park have been used for an exhibition [[Street circuit|street race]] of the [[FIA GT1 World Championship]] in 2011, after a race at [[Goldenport Park Circuit]] in the vicinity. It again served as an Olympic Park when Beijing hosted the [[2022 Winter Olympics]] and the [[2022 Winter Paralympics]].

