Chronological summary of the 2022 Winter Olympics

{{short description|None}}

{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2022}}
{{2022 Winter Olympics}}

This is a chronological summary of the major events of the [[2022 Winter Olympics]] in [[Beijing]] and venues near neighboring towns of [[Yanqing District|Yanqing]] and [[Chongli District|Chongli]] in the [[China|People's Republic of China]]. Competition began on 2 February with the first matches in the group stages of the [[Curling at the 2022 Winter Olympics|curling]] events. The [[2022 Winter Olympics opening ceremony|opening ceremony]] was held two days later on 4 February. The last day of competition and the [[2022 Winter Olympics closing ceremony|closing ceremony]] were on 20 February.

The games featured 109 events in 7 different sports, encompassing a total of 15 disciplines. New events included [[Freestyle skiing at the 2022 Winter Olympics – Men's big air|men's]] and [[Freestyle skiing at the 2022 Winter Olympics – Women's big air|women's]] big air freestyle skiing, [[Bobsleigh at the 2022 Winter Olympics – Women's monobob|women's monobob]], mixed team competitions in [[Freestyle skiing at the 2022 Winter Olympics – Mixed team aerials|freestyle skiing aerials]], [[Ski jumping at the 2022 Winter Olympics – Mixed team|ski jumping]], and [[Snowboarding at the 2022 Winter Olympics – Mixed team snowboard cross|snowboard cross]], and the [[Short track speed skating at the 2022 Winter Olympics – Mixed 2000 metre relay|mixed relay in short track speed skating]].

About 91 [[National Olympic Committee]]s qualified athletes, with [[Haiti at the 2022 Winter Olympics|Haiti]] and [[Saudi Arabia at the 2022 Winter Olympics|Saudi Arabia]] each making their Winter Olympics debuts. As a result of the 2020 ruling by the [[Court of Arbitration for Sport]] on the [[Russian doping scandal]], Russian athletes competed in both the [[2020 Summer Olympics]] and the 2022 Winter Olympics under the acronym "[[Russian Olympic Committee athletes at the 2022 Winter Olympics|ROC]]" after the name of the [[Russian Olympic Committee]], and under the flag of the Russian Olympic Committee.

