{{2022 Winter Olympics}}
The '''2022 Winter Olympics torch relay''' was run from 18 October 2021 until 4 February 2022. After it was lit in [[Olympia, Greece]], the torch traveled to Athens in a car. and was handed to Beijing on 20 October. The Chinese leg ended in [[Beijing National Stadium]], at the end of the opening ceremony. On 20 October 2021, it was announced that the Chinese leg had only three days, following a series of displays of the flame in cities around Beijing.The physical relay started on 2 February, at the morning of the first day of the [[Chinese New Year]] as stage 3. Unlike the previous relays, the relay only visited the three venues clusters, the main sights of [[Beijing]] and the city of [[Zhangjiakou]]. The final torch was lit by long-distance runner [[Dinigeer Yilamujiang|Dilnigar Ilhamjan]] (Dinige'er Yilamujiang) and nordic combined Zhao Jiawen.

